In all this there is of course no direct or positive evidence that Virgil intended anything more than a song on the death and glorification of Daphnis, suggested (as we have seen) by Theocritus; but the reference to Caesar is, regarding all the cir- cumstances of the time, highly probable and deserves at least serious consideration.

The scenery, as elsewhere, is Sicilian rather than Italian, and apparently borrowed from Theocritus.
